.TH PRT-DEP 8 "prt-#VERSION# Manual"
.SH NAME
prt-dep \- Print dependencies for a port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B prt dep
.B [-v|-vv] [--path]
.B [--all]
.B [--tree]
.B [--recursive]
.B [--full]
.I PORT
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print dependencies for a
.IR PORT .
It looks in all directories specified in \fC/etc/prt.conf\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v
Show version in the listing.
.TP
.B \-vv
Show version and description in the listing.
.TP
.B \-\-path
Show port path in the listing.
.TP
.B \-\-all
List all ports, not only installed.
.TP
.B \-\-tree
Print a nicely indented tree of the \fIPORT\fR dependencies.
.TP
.B \-\-recursive
Print a recursive list of dependencies.
In case \fB--tree\fR was specified, subtrees already shown are marked
with '-->' to save some space. If \fB--tree\fR option wasn't specified,
dependencies already shown aren't displayed.
In order to show them all, add the \fB--full\fR switch.
.TP
.B \-\-full
If recursive mode was set, show all dependencies.
